cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "duplex-bol: a full-duplex Pakistani-Urdu speech-to-speech research scaffold"
message: "If you use this scaffold or its data-engineering tooling, please cite it."
type: software
authors:
  - name: "duplex-bol contributors"
repository-code: "https://github.com/maidah-binte-tariq/duplex-bol"
license: Apache-2.0
keywords:
  - urdu
  - speech-to-speech
  - full-duplex
  - barge-in
  - moshi
abstract: >-
  A one-week proof-of-concept scaffold for a full-duplex Pakistani-Urdu voice
  agent. Provides Urdu text normalization, audio/manifest data engineering,
  two-party stereo corpus synthesis for Moshi-style fine-tuning, a deterministic
  barge-in orchestrator for a streaming ASR→LLM→TTS cascade, and a WER/latency
  evaluation harness.
